<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFE7683A459A3388B9A6F94C" blockId="18.[151,1437,1414,1729]" pageId="18" pageNumber="301">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE7683A459A3388BB40F910" bold="true" box="[199,315,1667,1693]" pageId="18" pageNumber="301">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFE7683A44183388B816F910" baseAuthorityName="Neboiss" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[325,621,1667,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Polycentropodidae" genus="Nyctiophylax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="301" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhamphodes">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE7683A44183388B816F910" box="[325,621,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="301">Nyctiophylax rhamphodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally recorded from seven sites in Kakadu NP, NT (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFE7683A401D3388BAA8F94C" author="Neboiss, A." pageId="18" pageNumber="301" pagination="191 - 205" refId="ref15513" refString="Neboiss, A. (1994) A review of the genus Paranyctiophylax Tsuda from Sulawesi, Papua New Guinea and northern Australia (Trichoptera: Polycentropodidae). Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 54, 191 - 205. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 1994.54.09" type="journal article" year="1994">Neboiss 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Here, the NT endemic species is recorded from a further eight sites.
</paragraph>
